I still don't see what is "attractive" about these things - they're oddly proportioned and made up of every single contemporary supercar design cliche in the industry. How many more generic "stealth airplane" angular scoops and lines and cuts can they tack on??? It's every bit as 'gold chain & New Balances' gaudy as the C7!

Also, how anyone can say that the C7 look like an evolution of the C5, I have no idea; completely different design language, the C5 is very slim, clean, and sleek, while the C7 is busy and gaudy. In fact, I don't know how the hell the C8 styling could be called anything other than "mid-engine C7". The C7 is FAR closer in style to the C8 than the C5, I really don't understand how Doug could somehow think otherwise.
